# Ability Name			Output Name						Category of Ability		Type						Visible	Description																																																																																													Source Page
Command Own Kind			OUTPUTNAME:Command creatures of its kind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	DESC:%1/day a mount can use this ability to command any normal animal of approximately the same kind as itself, as long as the target creature has fewer Hit Dice than the mount. This ability functions like the command spell, but the mount must make a DC 21 Spellcraft check to succeed if the target is being ridden at the time. If the check fails, the ability does not work that time, but it still counts against the mount's daily uses. Each target may attempt a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 paladin's level + paladin's Cha modifier) to negate the effect.|SMLevel/2	SOURCEPAGE:p.35
Devotion											CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An animal companion gains a +4 morale bonus on Will saves against enchantment spells and effects.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Empathic Link ~ Special Mount	OUTPUTNAME:Empathic Link			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The paladin has an empathic link with her mount to a distance of 1 mile. The paladin cannot see through the mount's eyes, but the two can communicate empathically. Note that even intelligent mounts see the world differently from humans, so misunderstandings are always possible.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.35
Improved Speed										CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The mount's speed increases.																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.35
Link												CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A druid can handle her animal companion as a free action, or push it as a move action, even if she doesn't have any ranks in the Handle Animal skill. The druid gains a +4 circumstance bonus on all wild empathy checks and Handle Animal checks made regarding an animal companion.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Share Saving Throws									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality			VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The familiar uses either the familiar's base save bonus or the master's, whichever is better. The familiar uses its own ability modifiers to saves, and it doesn't share any of the other bonuses that the master might have on saves.																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.35
Share Spells										CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A druid may cast a spell with a target of "You" on her animal companion (as a touch range spell) instead of on herself. A druid may cast spells on her animal companion even if the spells normally do not affect creatures of the companion's type (animal).																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.26

